-{"id":"franken_networkx-n2oc","title":"parity: MultiGraph and MultiDiGraph degree() should be callable","description":"MultiGraph.degree() and MultiDiGraph.degree() currently expose non-callable degree view objects, so callable forms like list(G.degree()), G.degree('a'), and G.degree('a', weight='weight') raise TypeError. Upstream NetworkX supports the same callable degree() contract on both multigraph families. Match that behavior.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:26:48.430361644Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:26:48.430361644Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
