 {"id":"franken_networkx-n2pm","title":"parity: shortest_simple_paths should reject multigraphs","description":"shortest_simple_paths currently yields paths on MultiGraph inputs, but NetworkX raises NetworkXNotImplemented('not implemented for multigraph type'). This parity break shows up for unweighted and string-weight calls, and callable weights currently fail with a PyO3 TypeError instead of the upstream multigraph guard. Match NetworkX's multigraph error contract before any weight-specific handling.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T06:20:46.670801554Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T16:01:26.687489691Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T16:01:26.685612718Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
